<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-458-890  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 458 890.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  May 22 1990 v7 n20 p15(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tektronix offers color PostScript for under $8,000. (Tektronixintroduces Phaser PX color PostScript printer) (productannouncement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tektronix Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    TEK.andO;Product:   Tektronix Phaser PX (Computer printer) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     PrintersLow CostProduct IntroductionColor.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Prices for color PostScript printers will slide down a notch this week whenTektronix Inc. announces a model designed to bring high-end color printing toa wider range of corporate users.andM;The company's new Phaser PX printer, available now, sports aPostScript-compatible controller, 6M bytes of memory, a 300-dot-per-inchresolution and a $7,995 price tag.andM;The software included with the Phaser PX allows users to select serial,parallel or AppleTalk ports to output data, enabling the printer to be usedin mixed PC and Macintosh environments.andM;&quot;The printer is built to be shared but priced so it doesn't have to be,&quot; saidA.J.andP;  Rogers, marketing manager for Tektronix in Wilsonville, Ore.andM;The Phaser PX's price tag marks a new low for color PostScript printers,according to Michael Weiss, president of MWA Consulting in Palo Alto, Calif.andO;Competitive units from QMS Inc. and NEC Technologies Inc. cost $9,995 each,he said.andM;Tektronix equipped the new printer with a Windows Printer Description file togive users access to the color PostScript printer driver in Windows 3.0.andP;  Theprinter also includes the Hewlett-Packard Graphics Language for printingplotter files.andM;Tektronix can be contacted at (800) 835-6100.andO;</TEXT></DOC>